text:
Cool DMC facts and stuff:

- most of Dante’s Sin DT moves are references to his moves from DMC1. The move Luce is a reference to Sparda’s pistols, Luce and Ombra.

- Cavalier Angelo’s boss introduction is also a reference to DMC1, where Trish rode a motorcycle through Dante’s store and then threw it at him.

- V’s demons are actually attached to his hair and tats. That’s why he’s missing them during the boss rush.

- It’s a running joke in the series that Dante gets impaled by his own sword in each game.

- Each DMC game has their own boss rush level. 5’s is interesting because it has V fight Nero and Dante’s bosses (except for Gilgamesh, because there’s no way to get those mechanics to work for V).

- Speaking of Gilgamesh, it’s actually the fist-and-boots weapon from DMC4. However, because of 4’s budget restraints, Gilgamesh is dropped from a plant-snake lady instead of a more appropriate demon.

- King Cerberus is a reference to the Cerberus fight from DMC3. That Cerberus was purely an ice doggo, so you only got the ice-chucks instead of the absolute beast that is King Cerberus in this game.

- When King Cerberus switches to fire and ice forms, he has the chance to reference Berial and Bael, two bosses from DMC4.

- Dr. Faust is a reference to the Faust enemies from DMC4, and also provide a slight hint as to who Nico’s dad is.

text:
I know what you mean, Gura; it can just be more stress to always try and believe that tomorrow will be a better day, and it hurts more to be let down by another bad day. It's good to just breathe through each day, take it for what it is, and move forward. Sometimes though, it can get you stuck in a mindset where you start to lose hope that SOME day will be better--but it will be. Whatever sadness or worries you're facing now will eventually pass. Whatever happiness you feel like you're missing will eventually come home. So even if today was bad and you don't know if tomorrow will be better, breathe through the rough times and smile when you can--but don't ever lose faith that things will get better. You don't have to believe in karma, or anything like that. Just that people will see you, will find you, who can understand your worries and pain and love you for who you are, and can help you do the same. 

ANYWAY, that's a lot of mushy stuff, but if it can help you (or anyone else) then it was worth it. I had a really emotional day myself, and the funny laughs and cozy Little Shark energy were a real blessing tonight. I really enjoy watching you play this game, not just for the cheesy jokes and awesome action, but because you being attached to the characters is really cute and sweet. I can't wait for whatever craziness you have planned for us for the BATHTUB PIZZA STREEEEEEAM. Remember to be kind to yourself, try to smile when you can, and never lose hope in better days. Love you, Gura. <3
